WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:08.666
We introduce RoMo, a large-scale, richly organized dataset and semantic taxonomy for human motion generation.

2
00:00:08.666 --> 00:00:15.000
RoMo is organized by a novel hierarchical taxonomy spanning 54 broad categories...

3
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:18.300
...and over 2,000 fine-grained subcategories.

4
00:00:18.300 --> 00:00:25.500
We utilized L-L-M to synthesize over 58,000 diverse search queries to retrieve in-the-wild videos.

5
00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:28.966
Starting with over fourteen years of raw footage

6
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:33.266
we applied a rigorous, taxonomy-aware filtering pipeline.

7
00:00:33.266 --> 00:00:38.700
We distilled this massive input down to the top 1% of high-fidelity motion data.

8
00:00:38.700 --> 00:00:46.400
We employ Qwen3-VL for temporal semantic segmentation, slicing video into atomic action spans.

9
00:00:46.400 --> 00:00:52.500
We extract 3D motion sequences using the state-of-the-art G-V-H-M-R estimator

10
00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:57.333
...converting video into accurate, world-grounded 3D human motion.

11
00:00:57.333 --> 00:01:04.033
RoMo captures a vast range of behaviors, from fitness and gaming to sports and outdoor activities.

12
00:01:04.166 --> 00:01:09.500
Each sequence is paired with rich text descriptions capturing the nuance of the action.

13
00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:17.233
The final dataset features over 820,000 motion clips and 1,237 hours of data.

14
00:01:17.366 --> 00:01:24.766
We invite you to explore more results in the HTML page and our open-source Motion Toolbox in the supplementary material.
